# Chapter 1 Ecology sims

When changing Grade 8 **Ch 1 – Ecology** simulations (carbon–oxygen, food web, ecological pyramid, predator–prey, global warming):

1. **Open like PhET Color Vision** — Catalog cards open SceneryStack HTML (`sceneryHtml`) in a new tab so the sim fills the window with a dark canvas and its own bottom nav (title / home / sound). Do not letterbox in a site header/footer. React-only sims use full-bleed `/run/:id`.

2. **Relatable images, not abstract shapes** — Organisms and key scene objects use the ecology icon art (`EcologyArt.ts` / friendly SVGs: rabbit, fox, plant, tree, factory, Earth, etc.). Prefer pictures students recognize over plain circles or diamonds.

3. **Self-explanatory on screen** — Live **NOW / WHY / Next** (or equivalent) captions, plain Class-8 language (rabbits/foxes, not only “prey/predator”), and graph legends that say what green/red mean. Depth stays in the model; the UI narrates it clearly.

4. After SceneryStack package changes, rebuild offline HTML (`build:*-offline` / package `npm run build`) so `public/downloads/*` stays in sync.
